I think this tool would be really beneficial in a clinical context provided it had the relevant clinical details. As opposed to making a recommendation, i think this tool would be useful for highlighting potential patients that may be suitable for an oral switch.

The key piece of information missing from some of the vignettes was what the diagnosis was. I was often unwilling to make a decision without knowing what infection was being treated. Determination of diagnosis would be a key area for AI in the future.

I think that much of the decision making around IV-to-oral switch is centred on the infection diagnosis and antimicrobial therapy (in combination with the patient's vital signs and subjective improvement). Infection diagnosis did not seem to feature in the AI decision making which would be a concern for users. Also, the use of "prediction correct" in the AI table could have better terminology as implies that this is what "should have happened", rather than "what actually did happen".
